<HEADLINE>
<P>
A PREGNANT QUESTION FOR THE FIRST LADY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As Hillary Rodham Clinton's spokesman, Neel Lattimore fields questions from 
inquiring minds every day.But he drew the line at this tabloid query: Is the 
First Lady pregnant? 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't have the guts to ask her," he said with a laugh. 
</P>
<P>
 A tabloid paper that hits the stands this week reports that "insiders" tell a 
British biographer Mrs. Clinton is due in April. The First Lady turns 47 next 
month. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is the same publication that said she adopted a space alien baby," 
Lattimore said. "If they already have a space alien baby, I don't know if they 
need another one." 
</P>
