<TEXT>
<P>
 Todos Hermanos, a recently formed gang prevention program in Costa Mesa, is 
sponsoring a softball game today aimed at striking out gang violence. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will be at Lions Park from noon to 5 p.m. The first pitch will be 
thrown out by Newport-Mesa Unified School District Supt.Mac Bernd. 
</P>
<P>
 Former, current and wanna-be gang members, parents, City Council members, 
students and a number of local youth organizations will take part in the event, 
said Roy Alvarado, president of the nonprofit Todos Hermanos. 
</P>
<P>
 "The purpose is to bring the community together to support each other and 
become friends," Alvarado said. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is free and all proceeds from food sales will benefit the group, 
which provides a variety of gang prevention activities. MIMI KO 
