<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ever get the feeling that you are being watched while waiting for a traffic 
light to turn green in Irvine? 
</P>
<P>
 In a way, you are. 
</P>
<P>
 The eight busiest Irvine intersections are monitored by closed-circuit 
cameras, linked to the Irvine Traffic Research and Control Center on the second 
floor of City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine traffic engineers change the timing of traffic signals from control 
center computer terminals to compensate for traffic jams. 
</P>
<P>
 Four more intersections will be monitored by the end of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 During the past 19 years, the number of traffic signals in Irvine has grown 
from 30 to 215. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Attention cat lovers. The place to be is at the Orange County Fairgrounds, 
where a cat show will be held from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The show, sponsored by The Perthshire Clan, will include contests for pedigree 
and non-pedigree felines. 
</P>
<P>
 An exhibition showcasing cat-related goods and services will also be held. 
</P>
<P>
 The show runs through Oct. 2. 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange County Fairgrounds is located at 88 Fair Drive in Costa Mesa. For 
more information, call (619) 598-5808. 
</P>
