<HEADLINE>
<P>
KANDALY TRIES TO END SLUMP IN SUPER DERBY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ever since hitting the jackpot in his first stakes, the Louisiana Derby, 
Kandaly has spent a long season collecting consolation prizes. 
</P>
<P>
 Kandaly will try to snap a six-race losing streak today in the $750,000 Super 
Derby XV at Louisiana Downs. 
</P>
<P>
 The morning line isn't exactly bubbling at his chances: He's the 8-1 fifth 
choice in the field of eight 3-year-olds going 1 1/4 miles. 
</P>
<P>
 The 2-1 favorite in the Grade I race is Soul Of The Matter, the winner of the 
San Felipe Stakes. 
</P>
<P>
 Meadow Flight, winner of the Flamingo Stakes and the Pennsylvania Derby, is 
listed as the second favorite at 5-2 in the Grade I race for 3-year-olds at 1 
1/4 miles. 
</P>
<P>
 Concern, the Arkansas Derby winner, is at 3-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Kandaly has earned money in each of his 10 races. Even during his losing 
streak, he earned $146,190. 
</P>
