has refused 20th Century Industries' request to reconsider an Aug. 18 decision 
upholding Insurance Commissioner John Garamendi's rules for enforcing 
Proposition 103. The court's refusal to review its 7-0 ruling means that 
Woodland Hills-based 20th Century still owes $119 million in rebates to 
policyholders under the 1988 insurance rollback initiative. A spokesman said 
20th Century has not decided whether to appeal its defeat to the U.S. Supreme 
Court and that it is continuing discussions with the Insurance Department about 
a possible settlement. 
