<TEXT>
<P>
 A 26-year-old Moorpark man who has been unconscious since he hit his head 
during a fall in a concrete drainage ditch last weekend remains hospitalized 
and has fallen into extremely critical condition, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Rafael Soto is in the intensive care ward of Simi Valley Hospital, where he 
was admitted Sunday with a severe head injury, hospital officials and police 
said. 
