<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; NEW RESOLUTION ON PROP. 187 APPROVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Putting financial and legal concerns ahead of humanitarian arguments, the 
Ventura school board has approved a resolution opposing Proposition 187 that is 
substantially different than the statement it initially considered. 
</P>
<P>
 The board voted 5 to 0 to oppose the November ballot measure that would deny 
public education, non-emergency health care and other social services to 
illegal immigrants.But the unanimous vote came only after the board agreed to 
revise the resolution it had considered two weeks before. 
</P>
<P>
 The board initially discussed a resolution opposing the measure because "it is 
in the best interest of the general public to educate all children, citizens or 
undocumented immigrants, when considering the alternative cost to the taxpayer 
if they are not provided this opportunity." MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
