<HEADLINE>
<P>
WALSH, WILLIS LEAD BYU OVER UTAH STATE, 34-6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Walsh threw for two touchdowns and Jamal Willis ran for two scores as 
Brigham Young rolled past penalty-plagued Utah State, 34-6, Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The game was moved up a day to avoid conflicting with conferences being held 
by BYU's parent Mormon Church. 
</P>
<P>
 Walsh, who left the game with one quarter to play, completed 17 of 27 passes 
with no interceptions for 306 yards for BYU (4-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Willis was held to 51 yards by Utah State but still reached a school-record 34 
career touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Utah State (1-4) was penalized nine times for 96 yards, including two 
unsportsmanlike conduct calls against Coach Charlie Weatherbie. 
</P>
