<HEADLINE>
<P>
WAKEFIELD KEYS WOODBRIDGE'S 24-10 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GABE LACQUES, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Theo Wakefield caught a touchdown pass, ran for one score and recovered two 
fumbles to lead Woodbridge to a 24-10 nonleague victory over Century on Friday 
at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Wakefield caught a screen pass from quarterback Brian Millat and broke several 
tackles, turning a short play into a 30-yard touchdown reception, giving the 
seventh-ranked Warriors a 17-10 lead with 3 minutes 9 seconds left in the 
second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Then, on Woodbridge's second possession of the second half, Wakefield ran 79 
yards on a sweep for his second touchdown and a 24-10 lead with 3:01 left in 
the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge's defense took care of the rest. It sacked Century quarterback 
Stanley Villanueva six times, and held the Centurions to 26 yards rushing. 
Justin Dufour had three sacks for Woodbridge. 
</P>
<P>
 Villanueva, who entered the week as the third-leading passer in the county, 
completed 11 of 23 passes for 139 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 He scored the Centurions' only touchdown on a one-yard sneak with 8:56 left in 
the second quarter, giving Century (2-2) a 10-3 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge (4-0) scored on its next drive, going 74 yards in seven plays. 
Millat hit Nate Perrizo with a short pass at the Century 30-yard line, and 
Perrizo broke an attempted tackle by Rolando Cortez and turned the play into a 
41-yard touchdown to tie the score. 
</P>
<P>
 Wakefield led Woodbridge with 92 yards rushing in eight carries. Millat 
completed eight of 16 passes for 121 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Beau Wallace was Century's leading rusher with 32 yards in 14 carries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
