 Sunny Hills converted three turnovers into touchdowns and running back Chris 
Velotta rushed for 92 yards as the Lancers defeated Mission Viejo, 27-21, for 
their first victory of the season, Friday night at Buena Park High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers (1-3) got on the board first as Velotta broke three tackles for a 
15-yard touchdown run.Two series later, Sunny Hills linebacker Dereck Cretz 
intercepted Diablo quarterback Austin Moherman's pass at the Mission Viejo 16 
and powered his way into the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
 After Mission Viejo fumbled the ensuing kickoff, Lancer quarterback Greg 
Gearand hit wide receiver Jeff Renaud for a 25-yard pass in the corner of the 
end zone. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing, 20-0, Mission Viejo finally got on the board with nine seconds 
remaining in the first half when Diablo running back Todd Fielding scored on a 
three-yard run to cap a five-play, 50-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
 At the opening of the third quarter, Mission Viejo committed yet another 
turnover as Fielding mishandled the pitch into the backfield, allowing the 
Lancers to recover. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers' Gearand completed a six-play, 51-yard drive with an eight-yard 
touchdown run. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo tried to come back on wide receiver Ryan Ballas' eight catches 
for a 126 yards -- including 19-yard and a 30-yard touchdown catches late in 
the game. MICHAEL LYNCH 
