<BYLINE>
<P>
By DALE RUHE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Katella High's Josh Welton missed a 25-yard field goal attempt as time 
expired, giving Brea-Olinda a 7-6 victory in a nonleague game Friday night at 
Wildcat Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Welton had brought the Knights to within a point when he caught a nine-yard 
touchdown pass from quarterback Sal Viramontes.The play came with 4 minutes 14 
seconds left in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 The snap was bad on the Knights' extra-point attempt, and holder Chris Marquez 
picked up the ball, but his pass into the end zone fell incomplete. 
</P>
<P>
 Katella (0-4) got the ball back with 1:58 left after Brea (3-1) punted from 
its own nine-yard line. The Knights took over on the Brea 43. 
</P>
<P>
 Viramontes connected on first-down passes of 18 yards to Timmy Ho and 17 yards 
to Dan Schmidt before the Knights ran the clock down to three seconds. 
</P>
<P>
 Welton's kick was wide right. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea broke the scoreless tie with 1:09 left in the first half. Jerome Owens 
scored on a three-yard touchdown run up the middle. Owens led all rushers with 
102 yards in 27 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea limited Katella to 32 yards in total offense in the first half, but the 
Knights moved the ball much better in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Viramontes was seven of 14 for 133 yards. DALE RUHE 
