<P>
GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE; VAQUEROS RUSH PAST PACIFICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICK CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sparked by three touchdowns and 143 yards rushing by tailback Chris Young, 
Rancho Alamitos rolled to a 42-16 victory over Pacifica Friday night in the 
Garden Grove League opener for both teams. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vaqueros (2-2) scored all six touchdowns on the ground, rushing for 332 
yards at Bolsa Grande High. 
</P>
<P>
 The game was delayed twice in the fourth quarter by injuries. Rancho Alamitos 
lineman Jason Bluestein left with thumbs up after suffering a back injury. But 
Pacifica wide receiver Mike Parsons was carried off on a stretcher with head 
and neck injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos led the entire game, scoring first on Young's 13-yard run. A 
26-yard field goal by Greg Chow cut the lead to 7-3 at the end of the first 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Following a short Pacifica punt, Young gave Rancho Alamitos a 14-3 advantage, 
running 63 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos' Jeff Turbarg returned an interception 55 yards to the 
Pacifica three-yard line set up Kevin Allen's three-yard scoring run. Rancho 
Alamitos led, 21-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica narrowed the margin to 21-10 when Brian Walker recovered a muffed 
handoff in the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica's rushing game was led by Tommy Summers, who had 25 carries. His 
five-yard touchdown run with 6:41 left in the game closed the gap to 28-16. 
</P>
<P>
 Vaquero sophomore reserve Leo Kosi quickly made it a rout again with touchdown 
runs of 43 and 49 yards. RICK CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
