<P>
DUCK FANS ASKED TO HOLD TICKETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fans with tickets to the three Mighty Duck home games that have been postponed 
due to the NHL labor dispute are being asked to hold the tickets until games 
are rescheduled or canceled, the team said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Since the NHL intends to play a full 84-game season schedule and the Stanley 
Cup playoffs, the tickets purchased for those games will be honored," Mighty 
Ducks President Tony Tavares wrote in a letter to fans. 
</P>
<P>
 The affected home games are Oct. 9 against Calgary, Oct. 12 against Vancouver 
and Oct. 14 against Boston, all at The Pond. 
</P>
<P>
 "If at a later date, NHL games are canceled and not rescheduled, the Mighty 
Ducks will issue a ticket return policy," the letter said. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with questions can contact the team at (714) 704-2701. ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
