<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: HUNTINGTON PARK; 2 HELD 
IN SHOOTING OF OFF-DUTY OFFICER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men were arrested on suspicion of attempted murder and robbery after an 
off-duty Los Angeles Police Department officer was shot while using a pay phone 
Thursday night in Huntington Park, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 22-year-old officer, whose namewas not released, was shot in the legs but 
not seriously wounded in the attack in the 3000 block of Florence Avenue, said 
Sgt. Ron Spear of the Sheriff's Department.The officer had been using the phone 
when two men approached and one thrust a gun in his stomach, Spear said. 
</P>
<P>
 A struggle followed and the suspect's gun went off, striking both the 
officer's legs, Spear said. The officer returned gunfire as the two men fled. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Park police later arrested Aaron Ibarra, 31, after he sought 
treatment for a gunshot wound at Martin Luther King/Drew Medical Center. He was 
in custody and in stable condition Friday at Los Angeles County-USC Medical 
Center, Spear said. 
</P>
<P>
 An investigation led to the arrest of Freddie Santiago, 25, at a home in South 
Gate. Santiago is suspected of driving the getaway vehicle, a red Blazer that 
had been reported stolen in Los Angeles, Spear said. 
</P>
<P>
 A third suspect was being sought, but details about his role in the attack 
were not available. 
</P>
<P>
 The officer was treated at County-USC Medical Center and released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
