<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: NORTH HILLS; GROUP DONATES VANS TO MEDICAL CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANTONIO OLIVO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Disabled American Veterans has donated two new shuttle vans to the 
Sepulveda Veterans Medical Center in North Hills to use for transporting 
disabled veterans to and from the facility. 
</P>
<P>
 The medical center's shuttle fleet, now at four, serves an average of 200 to 
300 veterans who sustained a disabling injury while on active duty. 
</P>
<P>
 The shuttle program was initiated in 1987, when budget constraints forced the 
medical center to eliminate vouchers disbursed to patients needing 
transportation to the hospital or clinic. 
</P>
<P>
 Operated by a corps of 25 volunteers under the supervision of a local DAV 
transportation coordinator, the vans run routes in the San Fernando Valley, 
Antelope Valley, Simi Valley and other parts of Ventura County weekdays from 8 
a.m. to 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 To schedule an appointment for shuttle service, call (818) 895-9408 for the 
San Fernando Valley, (805) 974-0448 for the Lancaster area, (805) 526-9237 for 
Simi Valley and (805) 385-8500 for other Ventura County communities. 
Appointments must be made three days in advance. 
</P>
<P>
 Those wishing to volunteer for the program should call (818) 895-9408. ANTONIO 
OLIVO 
</P>
</TEXT>
