<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; 
PHILANTHROPY AWARD TO HONOR STEVEN SPIELBERG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Director Steven Spielberg will be honored with the 1994 Chaim Weizmann Award 
for Philanthropic Leadership at a fund-raising dinner tonight in Beverly Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 The event, sponsored by the American Committee for the Weizmann Institute of 
Science, will honor Spielberg for his philanthropy and for raising awareness 
about the Holocaust. 
</P>
<P>
 The Israeli-based Weizmann Institute, founded in 1934, is a science and 
medical research organization. Tonight's $1,000-per-person dinner at the 
Beverly Hilton Hotel will mark the end of the American Committee's 50th 
anniversary celebration. Proceeds will benefit the institute. 
</P>
