<HEADLINE>
<P>
MONTCLAIR PREP PLAYERS SUSPENDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRYAN RODGERS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Montclair Prep Principal Vernon Simpson kept his word and suspended five 
football players for Friday's game against Kilpatrick. Akil Anderson, Demetrius 
Green, Kenny Peffer, Simone Shouhead and Langston Woodberry did not suit up for 
the Mounties' 26-14 loss. 
</P>
<P>
 The players were suspended for allegedly rough-housing a junior varsity player 
on the school bus after practice. Simpson said he received an anonymous letter 
about the situation. Coach George Giannini punished the players by making them 
run laps, but faculty members at the Van Nuys campus expressed concern that the 
punishment was too lenient. 
</P>
<P>
 Parents of at least two suspended players have stated that the suspensions 
were racially motivated. Of the five players suspended, three are black and two 
are white. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm offended about the implication that this had anything to do with race," 
Simpson said. "This was an equal-opportunity benching." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
