<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; NORTHWEST VALLEY CONFERENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES TEMMEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 San Fernando 36, Chatsworth 14 -- Larry Ford rushed for 105 yards in 10 
carries and scored twice to lead the Tigers (2-2, 1-0) at Chatsworth. 
</P>
<P>
 Ford's one-yard run in the second quarter capped a 17-play, 97-yard drive and 
gave San Fernando a 14-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Keijuan Douglas completed six of 14 passes for 105 yards, 
including a 21-yard pass to Larry Logan for the Tigers' first score of the 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 Lavell Thompson, who carried 14 times for 65 yards, scored on an 11-yard run 
in the third quarter to give San Fernando a 21-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 For Chatsworth (2-2, 0-1), running back Antwon Nelson gained 86 yards in 17 
carries and scored two touchdowns. Quarterback Aaron Hummel completed 11 of 18 
passes for 122 yards with one interception. JAMES TEMMEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
