<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; NORTHWEST VALLEY CONFERENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETER YOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cleveland 14, El Camino Real 7 -- Eric Brown blocked an El Camino Real punt 
and Jay Padilla recovered in the end zone early in the fourth quarter to lead 
Cleveland at Taft High. 
</P>
<P>
 With Cleveland (2-2, 1-0) trailing, 7-6, Padilla sacked El Camino Real 
quarterback Shaun Fishman at the Conquistadores' 15-yard line to force El 
Camino Real (1-3, 0-1) to punt. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown then blocked the punt and Padilla jumped on the ball for the score. 
Padilla ran for the two-point conversion. 
</P>
<P>
 El Camino Real had taken a 7-0 lead in the first quarter when Fishman hit 
receiver Jermel Jones on a seven-yard play. It was Fishman's only completion in 
nine attempts. Eyan Schriebman gained 82 yards in 18 carries. PETER YOON 
</P>
</TEXT>
