<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; MARMONTE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS TORRES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Royal 28, Channel Islands 0 -- Although Royal had 12 penalties for 110 yards 
and four turnovers, the Highlanders crushed the Raiders at Channel Islands. 
</P>
<P>
 Royal (3-1, 1-0) allowed only 97 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Highlanders rushed for 252 yards. Jerome Lee had 116 yards in 16 carries 
and scored on a 37-yard run in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Ty Russell recovered a fumble early in the first quarter on the Raiders' 41, 
and Royal scored five plays later on a three-yard run by Mike Reddington. 
</P>
<P>
 Christian Broussard scored on a 30-yard run in the third quarter and 
Dorirtyuan Stitt scored on a 56-yard run in the fourth quarter. It was Stitt's 
first carry of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Channel Islands (1-3, 0-1) was led by Tony Moore, who rushed for 45 yards in 
four carries. CHRIS TORRES 
</P>
</TEXT>
