<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; NONLEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAUREN PETERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 St. Francis 21, St. Monica 19 -- St. Monica failed on a two-point conversion 
pass that would have tied the score with one minute to play at St. Francis. 
Steve Pulley had connected with Jason Jones on a 16-yard pass to pull St. 
Monica within 21-19. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Francis (3-0-1) remained unbeaten against a team that had outscored its 
first three opponents by a 115-18 margin. 
</P>
<P>
 The decisive score came on a 30-yard touchdown pass from Brian Rucker to 
senior receiver Justin Vandercook with 10 minutes to play. Vandercook finished 
with six catches for 113 yards, and Karim Mahrous made two catches for 65 
yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Golden Knights' last score capped an 11-play, 72-yard drive after senior 
lineman Ernesto Lanuza recovered a fumble. 
</P>
<P>
 Rucker completed 15 of 22 for 208 yards and two touchdowns and junior Darin 
Maxwell rushed for 107 yards in 29 carries. LAUREN PETERSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
