<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; NONLEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG ANAPOL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canyon 13, Alemany 13 -- In a game marked by blown kicking opportunities, 
Alemany missed a 40-yard field-goal attempt with 35 seconds to play. Alemany 
also missed an extra point, and Canyon missed two field-goal tries and an extra 
point. 
</P>
<P>
 Running back Armone Lochard and quarterback Rudy Pantoja combined on a 72-yard 
touchdown pass play to pull Alemany (0-2-2) even in the third quarter. Pantoja 
completed 12 of 17 for 162 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Tight end Danny Arguella caught five passes for 31 yards and a second-quarter 
touchdown of seven yards. Lochard carried 12 times for 54 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon was paced by Jeff McKinley, who rushed for 132 yards in 25 carries. He 
scored on a one-yard run in the third quarter. McKinley accounted for 59 yards 
on the scoring drive, which gave the Cowboys (0-3-1) a 13-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon quarterback Ahjeron Palmer rushed for 75 yards in 12 carries. The 
Cowboys rushed for 243 yards. GREG ANAPOL 
</P>
</TEXT>
