<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; NONLEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Burbank 21, Arroyo 14 -- Quarterback Jason Jonas scored on his second attempt 
from the one-yard line with 58 seconds to play to give the Bulldogs (2-2) the 
victory at Arroyo. 
</P>
<P>
 The winning score capped a 14-play, 68-yard march that took more than seven 
minutes.Anson Beck set up the drive with an interception. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior running back Carlos Baker was the mainstay of the Bulldog attack, 
carrying 18 times for 120 yards and scoring two touchdowns. He scored from six 
yards at 2:19 in the first quarter to cap an eight-play, 72-yard drive, and 
returned a punt 66 yards down the left sideline with 43 seconds left in the 
first half to give Burbank a 13-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Jonas was nine of 14 for 96 yards with one interception. DARIN ESPER 
</P>
</TEXT>
