<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; NONLEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK CARULLI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake 56, Calabasas 26 -- Derek Lemkin completed 13 of 18 passes 
for 243 yards and four touchdowns to lead Harvard (2-1-1) at Calabasas. 
</P>
<P>
 Kadar Lewis caught touchdown passes of 35 and 22 yards from Lemkin and also 
returned an interception 32 yards for a score.Lewis finished with three 
receptions for 57 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Abed Abusaleh, who had 78 yards rushing, including scoring runs of three and 
six yards, caught a 14-yard touchdown pass from Lemkin to put Harvard-Westlake 
ahead, 36-14, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas (1-3) used two quarterbacks. Zak Lovenson completed eight of 11 for 
99 yards and one touchdown with two interceptions, and Patrick Smith threw 
touchdown passes of six and 35 yards to Jeff Arnell in the fourth quarter. 
FRANK CARULLI 
</P>
