<P>
 Burroughs 14, Glendale 3 -- Junior quarterback Mike Barrett tossed two 
touchdown passes in the first half to lead host Burroughs (2-2). 
</P>
<P>
 The Indians jumped out to a 6-0 lead on their first drive, scoring on a 
26-yard pass from Barrett to tight end Tony Listro. 
</P>
<P>
 Burroughs extended its lead late in the second quarter on a 23-yard touchdown 
pass from Barrett to wide receiver Scott Boldvich. 
</P>
<P>
 Barrett completed 11 of 22 passes for 137 yards and senior running back Carlos 
Moreno led Burroughs rushers with 74 yards in 23 carries. ERIC BARAD 
