<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANFORD KICK SAVES NEWBURY PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG MEADE, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chrissy Sanford kicked a 22-yard field goal as time expired to complete a wild 
rally as Newbury Park High edged Agoura, 15-13, in a Marmonte League opener at 
Newbury Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Panther quarterback Justin Vint completed a 43-yard pass to Eric Mahanke and a 
37-yard pass to Patrick Reddick to put Newbury Park (3-1) at the Charger 
four-yard line. An incomplete pass stopped the clock with five seconds 
remaining, setting the stage for Sanford's kick -- her first varsity field 
goal. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam Eyre's conversion following a four-yard scoring pass from Eric Fitzgerald 
to Roger Liang gave Agoura a 13-12 lead early in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Vint completed eight of 20 passes for 215 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
