<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; KILPATRICK STUNS MONTCLAIR PREP, 26-14 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRIAN CHALEW 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aided by three consecutive turnovers, Kilpatrick High raced to a 20-point 
first-quarter lead and upset Montclair Prep, 26-14, Friday night in a nonleague 
game at Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mounties (3-1), who had five players suspended before the game for hazing 
a fellow student, committed five turnovers (three fumbles and two 
interceptions). 
</P>
<P>
 Senior Mario Qualls rushed for 126 yards in 23 carries and scored three 
touchdowns for Kilpatrick (3-1), on runs of 26, 17 and 24 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Qualls' 26-yard run opened the scoring, and the Mustangs took a 14-0 lead when 
senior Cesar Cuevas connected with junior receiver Shawn Reed on an 11-yard 
pass play. Qualls dashed 17 yards for a touchdown to give Kilpatrick a 20-0 
lead, but Montclair Prep's Ziggy Jackson scored on a one-yard run late in the 
first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Teammate Henry Bell then scored from three yards, and the Mounties trailed, 
20-14, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Qualls added his third touchdown, a 24-yard run with less than a 
minute to play. BRIAN CHALEW 
</P>
</TEXT>
