<HEADLINE>
<P>
OXNARD GETS HUENEME ON RUN, 27-13 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRIAN SOBEL, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oxnard High ground out a 27-13 Channel League victory over Hueneme Friday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard's David Cameron rushed for 153 yards in 15 carries and scored on a 
52-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 Early in the third quarter, Oxnard's Jimmy Dang recovered Ronnie Jenkins' 
fumble. 
</P>
<P>
 Two plays later, Taj Lewis threw an eight-yard touchdown pass to Caleb 
Droughn, breaking a 13-13 tie. 
</P>
<P>
 Jenkins rushed for 184 yards in 20 carries and scored on a 30-yard run in the 
first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 He also scored a touchdown on a 15-yard pass from George Jones in the second 
quarter. 
</P>
