<HEADLINE>
<P>
CARR'S SNEAK MOVES BUENA PAST VENTURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON SANDS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quarterback Chris Carr's one-yard sneak late in the fourth quarter capped a 
16-play drive and gave Buena High a come-from-behind, 23-19 victory against 
Ventura in a Channel League opener Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Carr, a 5-foot-10, 165-pound senior, finished with 65 yards in 20 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena running back Josh Cross added 69 yards in nine carries and scored on a 
four-yard run in the third quarter to put Buena (3-1, 1-0 in league play) 
ahead, 15-12. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura (0-4, 0-1) reclaimed the lead, 19-15, early in the fourth quarter when 
Aaron Davis scored on a four-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura quarterback Erik Olson completed four of seven passes for 50 yards and 
one touchdown. Olson intercepted a Glenn Dudley pass and ran it back 55 yards 
for a touchdown in the second period. 
</P>
<P>
 Dudley completed seven of 16 passes for 103 yards and scored on a nine-yard 
run in the second quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
