<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANTELOPE VALLEY HAS HISTORY ON ITS SIDE AGAINST LOYOLA; FOOTBALL: ANTELOPES 
UPSET THE CUBS A YEAR AGO AND HOPE FOR SIMILAR RESULT TONIGHT AT GLENDALE HIGH. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL LAZARUS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Antelope Valley High football team hopes recent history repeats itself 
tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 In the third week of the season last year, the Antelopes suffered their first 
loss, falling to Bakersfield, then ranked No. 3 in the state. The next week, 
Antelope Valley rebounded to defeat Loyola, ranked sixth in the state, 15-14. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, Antelope Valley lost to Bakersfield, again ranked third in the 
state, 35-13, and must face eighth-ranked Loyola in a nonleague game at 7:30 
tonight at Glendale High. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley had been ranked 16th in the state before the Bakersfield game, 
but dropped out of the latest poll. 
</P>
<P>
 Loyola (3-0) posted an impressive 28-0 victory over previously unbeaten Saugus 
last week. Quarterback Kyle Speilbuhler completed 11 of 13 passes for 194 yards 
and three touchdowns against the Centurions. 
</P>
<P>
 Speilbuhler has completed 27 of 41 passes for 409 yards and four touchdowns. 
Dan Farmer has 13 receptions for 229 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Ellison leads the Cub running game with 234 yards in 32 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're going to have to play great for all four quarters if we want a chance 
to win," Antelope Valley Coach Brent Newcomb said. "We got a little break last 
year." 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, Antelope Valley was held to minus-six yards in the first half 
before scoring two fourth-quarter touchdowns to defeat Loyola for the first 
time in school history. 
</P>
<P>
 Before allowing five touchdowns against Bakersfield, Antelope Valley (2-1) had 
not yielded a point in victories over Hesperia, 8-0, and West Bakersfield, 
14-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Tailback Jermaine Lewis leads Antelope Valley with 217 yards in 46 carries. In 
last year's game, Lewis gained 108 yards in 20 carries, including a 62-yard 
run. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley quarterback Trymon Redick, who has been hampered by a finger 
injury, has completed four of 13 passes for 139 yards and one touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 In other 7:30 games tonight, Bishop Diego plays Santa Clara at Channel Islands 
High, Orange Lutheran plays Village Christian at Kennedy High, St. Genevieve 
and Murphy play at Jackie Robinson Stadium, and Bell-Jeff is at La Salle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Prep Sports 
</P>
</TYPE>
