<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LITTLE BIT OF HISTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mike Kane, a senior running back at Cal State Northridge, was fourth in 
regional voting for the Harlon Hill trophy in 1986, awarded annually to the top 
NCAA Division II football player. 
</P>
<P>
 Kane, an All-American, rushed for 1,565 yards and 14 touchdowns, both Western 
State Football Conference records. 
</P>
<P>
 His career rushing total is 3,572 yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
