<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; CAL LUTHERAN WOMEN FALL TO UC IRVINE SOCCER TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran surrendered four goals in the second half and lost a women's 
nonconference soccer match to UC Irvine at home Friday, 5-0. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anteaters (6-4) received goals from Tracie Ann Manz, Kim Kaitanjian, Kim 
Franzen, Amber Willingham and Christina Rivera. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine goalie Stephanie Boes recorded her fifth shutout of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran fell to 7-2. WATER POLO 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake 11, Calabasas 1 -- Senior hole man David Block scored four goals and 
Nick LeClerc added two for Westlake (6-2) in the first round of pool play at 
the Calabasas tournament. GIRLS' TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake 13, Marymount 5 -- Sophomore Jackie Gortman and freshman 
Lindsy Fordess lost only four games and swept all three of their doubles 
matches to lead Harvard-Westlake (6-0-1) in a nonleague match in Studio City. 
GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Oakwood d. Holy Martyrs, 12-15, 15-12, 15-8, 12-15, 15-1 -- Jessica Burtis had 
16 kills to lead the Gorillas in the Liberty League opener for both schools. 
</P>
